source.title: Lens tissue, LM
source.description: Light micrograph of lens tissue used for cleaning microscope lenses. Lens tissue is composed of microfibres which effectively remove dirt and oil from the surface of an optical component. This image was captured using brightfield illumination and detecting autofluorescence.
